### Web2RSS - Build RSS from configured sources
# Use with VS Code REST Client or curl. Ensure the server is running and `internal/web2rss/sources.yaml` exists.

### Build RSS for a configured source URL
GET http://localhost:8080/web2rss?url=https://www.lancedb.com/blog
Accept: application/rss+xml

# Expected: 200 and RSS XML payload

### Build RSS for an arbitrary page (may return 502 if not configured)
GET http://localhost:8080/web2rss?url=https://flink.apache.org/posts/
Accept: application/rss+xml

### Build RSS for another configured source URL
GET http://localhost:8080/web2rss?url=https://www.anthropic.com/engineering
Accept: application/rss+xml

### Build RSS for the newly added source URL
GET http://localhost:8080/web2rss?url=https://qoder.com/zh/blog
Accept: application/rss+xml

# Expected: 502 if the source is not configured in sources.yaml